plot: The allegiance of those closest to Tony is put to the test. A case of mistaken identity has serious ramifications.

The Beginning of the End. Phil finally puts the hits on the Soprano clan and Tony puts a hit on Phil which results in mistaken identity making everyone think its safe when its not and it results in a Death and Coma. After this happens Tony separates from his family to go into hiding as he sends Carmela, Janice, and the kids into hiding.—Shawn

Tony learns from Janice that Uncle Junior has run out of cash and can no longer afford to pay for his hospital fees. She and Bobby are prepared to contribute but Tony couldn't care less what happens to his uncle. At the mental hospital, AJ runs into Rihannon, someone he knew in high school. Phil Leotardo decides the time has come to get rid of Tony Soprano and orders his men to make it happen. They decide Tony, Sil and Bobby will be eliminated. FBI Agent Harris gives Tony a heads up about the possible hit. After Sil tells him that he's had to eliminate Bert Gervasi who was getting too close to the New York mobsters, Tony decides that they have to hit Phil first. Sil and Bobby agree and Tony wants them to bring in some friends from Italy to do the job for them. When the two hit men report the job done, they all relax but it turns out they hit the wrong guy and Phil is now in hiding. When they get Bobby and put Sil in the hospital, Tony goes into hiding as does his family.—garykmcd

Those closest to Tony have their allegiances tested as the New York - New Jersey conflict begins, both families put hits out on the other and a case of mistaken identity leads to serious ramifications for the Soprano clan. Meanwhile Dr. Melfi comes to a realisation about Tony with help from Dr. Kupferberg and AJ begins a new romance.—Cole Bailey

Phil is finally ready to wipe the Soprano Family off the map. After Phil puts the hit out on all of them Tony sends people to find Phil but end up killing the wrong person. When everyone thinks its safe, A death occurs and then a coma which cause Tony and Paulie and the remaining Soprano's to go into hiding.—Shawn
